1. *Pravite* li često ovakve greške? (Do you often *make* such mistakes?)
2. Šta *pravite* ovog vikenda? (What are you *doing* this weekend?)
3. Oni *prave* novu zgradu u centru grada. (They are *building* a new building in the city center.)
4. Kada *pravite* ispit? (When are you *taking* the exam?)
5. Ja ne mogu da *pravim* kolače, ali mogu da pečem hleb. (I can't *make* cakes, but I can bake bread.)
6. Zašto ne *pravite* više vežbi? (Why don't you *do* more exercises?)
7. Mi *pravimo* plan za letnji odmor. (We are *making* plans for our summer vacation.)
8. Da li je ovo pravo vreme da se *pravi* promena? (Is this the right time to *make* a change?)
9. Možemo *praviti* pauzu od petnaest minuta? (Can we take a fifteen-minute *break*?)
10. Kako se *pravilno* koristi ova mašina? (How is this machine *correctly* used?)

Note: The word "pravite" is a verb form of the verb "praviti", which means "to make" or "to do" in English. In these sentences, it is used in various tenses and forms, such as present tense, present continuous tense, imperative, and adverbial form.